Title: FIFA 20 Live Reveal – EA PLAY 2019
Comment:
Proposals to improve career mode

1-A bank account to evaluate the fortune of the coach and the player (according to the mode) and to be able to acquire goods and accessories
2-Customize the coach
3-Customize the player with his picture
4.Use the created player for manager mode
5-Bring back the tickets, the sponsors, the number of fans
6- Integrate the Africa Cup of Nations. It is an injustice not to see this competition.
7- Player mode: the possibility to start on the bench. and the ability to simulate matches with his player. integrate the possibility of becoming a captain.
text_en:
Proposals to improve career mode

1-A bank account to evaluate the fortune of the coach and the player (according to the mode) and to be able to acquire goods and accessories
2-Customize the coach
3-Customize the player with his picture
4.Use the created player for manager mode
5-Bring back the tickets, the sponsors, the number of fans
6- Integrate the Africa Cup of Nations. It is an injustice not to see this competition.
7- Player mode: the possibility to start on the bench. and the ability to simulate matches with his player. integrate the possibility of becoming a captain.

Title: FIFA 20 Live Reveal – EA PLAY 2019
Comment: This is the most underwhelming Fifa reveal I’ve seen. At some point in the last 3-4 years, it feels like EA stopped improving the gameplay as if they have already created the best simulation and they only add a couple of new mechanics to the game each year. But unfortunately it is far from perfect and they better start showing something different. I wish I didn’t say this but honestly I couldn’t tell any differences from Fifa 19 except a couple of new dribbling skills. Passing animations are still unrealistic, shooting animations are still picture perfect. Real football doesn’t look like this.
text_en: This is the most underwhelming Fifa reveal I’ve seen. At some point in the last 3-4 years, it feels like EA stopped improving the gameplay as if they have already created the best simulation and they only add a couple of new mechanics to the game each year. But unfortunately it is far from perfect and they better start showing something different. I wish I didn’t say this but honestly I couldn’t tell any differences from Fifa 19 except a couple of new dribbling skills. Passing animations are still unrealistic, shooting animations are still picture perfect. Real football doesn’t look like this.

Comment:
PLEASE fix pro clubs, few obvious changes that should have happened a long time ago!
-.- when you are on the screen to choose sides, people just stay in the middle the whole time without picking a side and waste everyone's time, and takes away from another person's slot to be able to join. maybe you can introduce a timed limit for ppl to choose sides? surely that will fix that.
-.- when you pick a position, if a team mate fails to pick a position whether trolling, or afk, it automatically chooses keeper for that player and it kills the game before it even starts, another way of wasting more time.
-.- the person who ends up being captain shouldn't be random because this effects drop in games if the player is new severely. maybe go with the highest rated player in the group or something equivalent.
-.- drop in matches should give you skill points, just how your club games do.


please and thank you,
text_en:
PLEASE fix pro clubs, few obvious changes that should have happened a long time ago!
-.- when you are on the screen to choose sides, people just stay in the middle the whole time without picking a side and waste everyone's time, and takes away from another person's slot to be able to join. maybe you can introduce a timed limit for ppl to choose sides? surely that will fix that.
-.- when you pick a position, if a team mate fails to pick a position whether trolling, or afk, it automatically chooses keeper for that player and it kills the game before it even starts, another way of wasting more time.
-.- the person who ends up being captain shouldn't be random because this effects drop in games if the player is new severely. maybe go with the highest rated player in the group or something equivalent.
-.- drop in matches should give you skill points, just how your club games do.


please and thank you,

Title: FIFA 20 Live Reveal – EA PLAY 2019
Comment: Shame on you EA this was absolutely rubbish. Just a few minutes of actual gameplay would have gone a long way, but no, just complete waffle. I like many others waited all day for this reveal, after already waiting for 3pm thinking we'd get more than just a trailer. This was the worst FIFA presentation at E3 for as long as I remember. Given the lack of new releases for EA this year, they could have dedicated a whole hour to FIFA 20, cut the waffle and gone straight to the stuff people want to know. Ditch the yearly title fee and make this game a monthly subscription and do the work you guys need to do to cater for all fans, from pro clubs to career mode players.
text_en: Shame on you EA this was absolutely rubbish. Just a few minutes of actual gameplay would have gone a long way, but no, just complete waffle. I like many others waited all day for this reveal, after already waiting for 3pm thinking we'd get more than just a trailer. This was the worst FIFA presentation at E3 for as long as I remember. Given the lack of new releases for EA this year, they could have dedicated a whole hour to FIFA 20, cut the waffle and gone straight to the stuff people want to know. Ditch the yearly title fee and make this game a monthly subscription and do the work you guys need to do to cater for all fans, from pro clubs to career mode players.

Comment: Suggestion: instead of pressing the shooting button before the ball arrives at the foot of player, press it just as it arrives. I think your years of playing PES have taught you that passing a lot infront of the goal would create goals. In FIFA sometimes its better to shoot when you are infront of the 18 yard box instead of going to the keeper. You were doing most of the things right in the match vs dortmund (i have just watched the stream till that match) but you are missing little things like the knowledge of when to shoot and also how to take corners. And i know watching Rob lose his temper is pretty funny to viewers but I have played fifa with a bad mood and guess what, you play worse when your head is not in it. Be a bit cool and sometimes forget the bad that have happened before and play with a calm head. I'll be rooting for you guys. Cheers

Comment: Hey Guys.  On a serious note, as much you don't want to.... Rob and Dave, watch this a few times and really look at what you are doing well and where you made silly mistakes.  I thought you guys did ok.  I'm absolutely not a pro but the things I'd take away would be there's a little bit of piddling about in defence so you get closed down and maybe a bit too much risk aversion up front.  Try to take a few more shots outside the box and if it goes wrong it goes wrong.  I think the practicing is really good and constructive but I don't think practicing on stream is good for Rob so get some more in but away from PS Access where you won't feel pressured or distracted as you know you're being watched.  Best of luck chaps, I'm genuinely cheering you on and I hope you do well.

Title: FIFA 20 - Final Preparations
Comment:
Hi Guys, I always miss the live streams but catch them when I can. Love your passion towards this and really hope you get a chance against the pros. 

The pro's tips are based on a slow game based on counter attacking football that only works if you two work in sync.

I'd suggest that you play a bit more loose. Meaning faster passing. Rob you're holding onto the ball in midfield too long waiting for Dave to get into the right positions or the right pass. This is easy to pick off as the other team force the wrong pass. Or worse get the ball. 

To counter this, remember that you've got players on the wing so those passes are on, if you want to catch their defenders out make those passes to the attackers faster. The game will always get the players in the right positions. Just trust that when you pass the  ball it'll make the on running player Dave or youself. 

On defending. I'd suggest not relying on L2 (jocking) too much. It squares your defenders and they can take you on and beat you... 1 on 1s etc. 
Counter this by holding L2 at the moment they try get past you, this puts  your defender in a defensive position at the moment they need to be. 
If you want to advance this, mix tapping x when defending instead of just holding L2. This makes your defender attempt a standing tackle. 
Exploit this even more when running next to a quick player to push them off the ball. Very helpful as most often they are weaker and easy to push off the ball. 

On goal kicks you can hold L2 to call  a defender closer to you. Use this carefully of course. But I'd suggest always looking to Mane on the wing on  goal kicks, he's got a better vertical jump and can win that against most right/ left backs. 

If you get that header to Firmino,  Mane will do an overlap. Headers can be through balls if you use triangle. Use that to get Mane running on the ring wing. 

I'd suggest you also swap Salah and Mane positionally. This helps as he can run down the left wing and deliver a cross on his stronger foot rather than cutting inside when he's normally on the right wing. This works for both Mane and Salah as they can strike the ball across the keeper (nice amount of power will result in a goal) if not you'll get a a second chance when the keeper spills it into the middle. 

Try pss the ball foward from the midfield using L1 to get a player running on. The pros may bite and try cover the runner which gives you more time on the ball and it you're closer to goal a chance at a shot on goal. 

If they don't bite, use L1 again for the second pass and you've got a nice triangle of players attacking the ball and moving forward. 

I'm not a pro but I've played the game enough to know the foundations. Hopefully people chime in on what they think and hopefully we see you guys give the pros a decent game. 

Apologies  for the essay everyone.

C'mon Acess!!

I'd suggest that you play a bit more loose. Meaning faster passing. Rob you're holding onto the ball in midfield too long waiting for Dave to get into the right positions or the right pass. This is easy to pick off as the other team force the wrong pass. Or worse get the ball. 

To counter this, remember that you've got players on the wing so those passes are on, if you want to catch their defenders out make those passes to the attackers faster. The game will always get the players in the right positions. Just trust that when you pass the  ball it'll make the on running player Dave or youself. 

On defending. I'd suggest not relying on L2 (jocking) too much. It squares your defenders and they can take you on and beat you... 1 on 1s etc. 
Counter this by holding L2 at the moment they try get past you, this puts  your defender in a defensive position at the moment they need to be. 
If you want to advance this, mix tapping x when defending instead of just holding L2. This makes your defender attempt a standing tackle. 
Exploit this even more when running next to a quick player to push them off the ball. Very helpful as most often they are weaker and easy to push off the ball. 

On goal kicks you can hold L2 to call  a defender closer to you. Use this carefully of course. But I'd suggest always looking to Mane on the wing on  goal kicks, he's got a better vertical jump and can win that against most right/ left backs. 

If you get that header to Firmino,  Mane will do an overlap. Headers can be through balls if you use triangle. Use that to get Mane running on the ring wing. 

I'd suggest you also swap Salah and Mane positionally. This helps as he can run down the left wing and deliver a cross on his stronger foot rather than cutting inside when he's normally on the right wing. This works for both Mane and Salah as they can strike the ball across the keeper (nice amount of power will result in a goal) if not you'll get a a second chance when the keeper spills it into the middle. 

Try pss the ball foward from the midfield using L1 to get a player running on. The pros may bite and try cover the runner which gives you more time on the ball and it you're closer to goal a chance at a shot on goal. 

If they don't bite, use L1 again for the second pass and you've got a nice triangle of players attacking the ball and moving forward.

Apologies  for the essay everyone.

Title: FIFA 20 - Final Preparations
Comment:
I'm no pro player, so I'll refrain from giving specific advices, I just wanted to point a few things out. 
Your attack isn't half bad (you just need to shoot more, instead of trying to pass your way into the net, especially when you're already inside the box), but you really need to practice your defense: try and keep LT pressed when 1 on 1, as your opponents seem to get past you far too easily; by pressing LT you should be able to put some space between yourself and the opposing player, react more quickly, and follow their movements, giving you time to precisely choose when to commit to the tackle.
Also, try not to move the defenders from their position, as this will ruin your team positioning, and often allow the opponent for a chance to break through. This is crucial when playing co-op.
text_en:

Title: FIFA 20 - Our Training Begins!
Comment:
People saying you should never quit etc. - it’s not that simple, sometimes when it comes to FIFA online it just isn’t fun. If connection is poor or you concede a couple of goals which are the fault of online play being a bit iffy (FIFA isn’t exactly designed to feel as though you always have full control defensively, especially online - that’s shown up quite embarrassingly with the esports aspect of the game where matches always seem to be high scoring) then why carry on? If you aren’t having fun you may as well just quit - the other team gets a win and you get to stop feeling irritated, you’d stop playing if you were offline.
It’s not the same with other games but FIFA is just no fun online when you’re down by more than a couple.
text_en:
People saying you should never quit etc. - it’s not that simple, sometimes when it comes to FIFA online it just isn’t fun. If connection is poor or you concede a couple of goals which are the fault of online play being a bit iffy (FIFA isn’t exactly designed to feel as though you always have full control defensively, especially online - that’s shown up quite embarrassingly with the esports aspect of the game where matches always seem to be high scoring) then why carry on? If you aren’t having fun you may as well just quit - the other team gets a win and you get to stop feeling irritated, you’d stop playing if you were offline.
It’s not the same with other games but FIFA is just no fun online when you’re down by more than a couple.

Comment: Fifa 20 ist noch nicht mal draußen und ich bin jetzt schon enttäuscht. Seit Fifa 2000 habe ich jedes Fifa gespielt, war eigentlich immer zufrieden. Aber dass jetzt Lizenzen für China League und 3. BL anscheinend wichtiger sind, als die Rechte an den Vereinsnamen verstehe ich nicht. Da kommen Mannschaften dazu die keine Sau kennt, aber im Gegenzug wird Juventus Turin nur billig kopiert, die Allianz Arena gibt es nicht mehr usw. Ich steh absolut nicht auf PES sondern auf Fifa. Aber wenn das so weiter geht wird mir wohl bald nichts mehr übrig bleiben. Ich schätze mal dass ich nicht der einzige bin der dieser Ansicht ist...
text_en: Fifa 20 is not even there and I'm already disappointed. Since Fifa 2000 I played every Fifa, was always satisfied. But now that licenses for China League and 3rd BL are apparently more important than the rights to the club name I do not understand. As teams come to know the no bad, but in return Juventus is copied only cheap, the Allianz Arena, there is no longer so I stand absolutely not on PES but to Fifa. But if this continues will be left me probably soon nothing more. I guess that I'm not the only one of this view is ...
